function.description:
Extract exif tags from a single file and returns an *OBJECT* containing the tags and their values.
## Projection The projection parameter accepts an OBJECT containing exif tag names as keys and a boolean flag as a value. This value denotes whether or not the tag should be included in the result or not. Whenever you specify a tag that should be included in the projection all other tags will default to false. ### Examples To get only the MIME Type tag:
{ "mimeType": true }
To get everything except the MIME Type:
{ "mimeType": false }
To get multiple tags:
{ "mimeType": true, "megapixels": true, "bitsPerSample": true }
